Commentary Text: Harpreet Brar to Markram, out Stumped!! Oof! That turned and bounced out of nowhere and what a good stumping that is from Jitesh Sharma. Drifts in on a good length on middle, then turns right across Markram who was flicking to leg, just over off-stump and Jitesh whips the bails off as Markram had his momentum dragged forward. The back foot couldn't get back in time. Fantastic piece of work from both Harpreet Brar and Jitesh. Markram walks off shaking his head. Markram st Jitesh Sharma b Harpreet Brar 21(17) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Harpreet Brar to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Livingstone!! You can't take on Livingstone at the ropes, you simply can't - this is one of the best of the season. Had to time his leap as he went two-handed and right in front of the ropes, took the catch and ensured that he didn't touch the advertisement skirtings. Needed something special to get rid of Abhishek, he was on song - saw the flight on this delivery and backed himself to clear long-on with the lofted drive, slightly dragged the shot and would have got away, if it was anyone other than Livingstone patrolling the deep. Abhishek Sharma c Livingstone b Harpreet Brar 43(32) [4s-5 6s-2]

The topspinner outside off, Bairstow reaches out to loft and it's straight up off a top-edge, Umran asks for the catch from short third and somehow drops it. Straight in and straight out. Disbelief on Bhuvi's face
